<h2>
    Alignment
</h2>

<p>
    Aligning text is done with the <code>text-align</code>
    property, which has a variety of styles like center, end, 
    start, etc..
</p>
<pre><code class="lang-css">p {
    text-align: center;
}
</code></pre>
@{
    string[] props = "start end left right center justify justify-all match-parent".Split(" ");
}
<ul>
@foreach (string prop in props)
{   
    <li>@prop</li>
}
</ul>

<div class="row">
@foreach (string prop in props)
{   
    
    <div class="shadow-sm bg-dark text-light p-3 mx-3 border rounded-3 col-sm-3" style="text-align: @prop;">
    <h3>@prop</h3> Ligula eu elementum. Vestibulum vehicula quis odio a sagittis. Ut luctus arcu non fringilla condimentum. Aenean at velit aliquam, aliquet turpis non, posuere nulla. Curabitur 
    </div>
}
</div>


<h2>
    Decoration
</h2>
<p>
    Text decoration controls the decorative lines of text. It is a shorthand 
    for the other text-decoration properties: 
    <ul>
        <li>
            text-decoration-color
        </li>
        <li>
            text-decoration-line
        </li>
        <li>
            text-decoration-style
        </li>
    </ul>
</p>
<pre><code class="lang-css">p{
    text-decoration: solid red underline;
}
</code></pre>
<p style="text-decoration: solid red underline; text-decoration-style: solid; text-decoration-color: red; text-decoration-line: underline;">
    Result text is underlined 
</p>
<pre><code class="lang-css">p {
    text-decoration-style: solid; 
    text-decoration-color: blue; 
    text-decoration-line: underline;
}
</code></pre>

<p style="text-decoration-style: solid; text-decoration-color: blue; text-decoration-line: underline;">
    Result text is underlined 
</p>

<pre><code class="lang-css">p {
    text-decoration-style: solid;
    text-decoration-color: red;
    text-decoration-line: line-through;
}
</code></pre>
<p style="text-decoration-style: solid; text-decoration-color: red; text-decoration-line: line-through;">
    Result crossed out
</p>

<h2>
    Transformation
</h2>
<p>
    The <code>text-transform</code> property makes text lowercase, uppercase or 
    both. 
</p>
<pre><code class="lang-css">p.upper{
    text-transform: uppercase;
}
</code></pre>
<p class="upper">
    Phasellus finibus ullamcorper neque.
</p>

<pre><code class="lang-css">p.lower{
    text-transform: lowercase;
}
</code></pre>
<p class="lower">
    Phasellus finibus ullamcorper neque.
</p>

<pre><code class="lang-css">p.title{
    text-transform: capitalize;
}
</code></pre>
<p class="title">
    Phasellus finibus ullamcorper neque.
</p>

<style>
p.upper{
    text-transform: uppercase;
}
p.lower{
    text-transform: lowercase;
}
p.title{
    text-transform: capitalize;
}
</style>

<h2>
    Spacing
</h2>
<p>
    Space can be added between words or between letters to increase 
    the readability or style of text. Some of the properties used in CSS are:
</p>
@{string[] s = "text-indent letter-spacing line-height word-spacing white-space".Split(" ");}
<ul>
    @foreach (string item in s)
    {
        <li>
            @item
        </li>
    }
</ul>

<h3>
    text-indent
</h3>
<p>
    An indent is a tab or set of spaces used before the first word 
    in a paragraph. 
</p>
<pre><code class="lang-css">
p {
  text-indent: 50px;
}
</code></pre>

<p style="text-indent: 50px;">
    Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Ut commodo libero a auctor tincidunt. Vestibulum non aliquam quam. Phasellus vel ex interdum, sagittis lectus id, imperdiet augue. Phasellus sed arcu tellus. Mauris a commodo leo, nec molestie enim. Class aptent taciti sociosqu ad litora torquent per conubia nostra, per inceptos himenaeos. Nullam fringilla placerat.
</p>

<h3>
    letter-spacing
</h3>
<p>
    Letter-spacing is the margin or space between each character in a word. 
</p>
<pre><code class="lang-css">
p {
  letter-spacing: 10px;
}
</code></pre>

<p style="letter-spacing: 10px;">
    Lorem ipsum
</p>

